abstract={In this paper, a novel GPS/INS integrated navigation system is proposed based on long and short term memory neural network (LSTM NN) for the unmanned aerial vehicle (UAV). UAV navigation system is a kind of nonlinear system usually consisting of inertial measurement unit (IMU) and global positioning system (GPS), which estimates the position and speed of the UAV by Kalman filters. However, the covariance noise parameter in Kalman filters is difficult to set manually, and moreover which should dynamically adapt to the UAV motion. LSTM NN has particular contextual memory units which can store the previous useful information automatically and is selected to design a novel end-to-end navigation method. To improve the accuracy of the model, different configurations of the LSTM NNs are used for comparison. Experimental results demonstrate that the proposed data-driven navigation method can achieve the online UAV position estimation well without building accuracy mathematical model and adjusting parameters manually.},
